# Next.js Best Practices

- Prefer Server Components by default. Use Client Components only for browser state or event handlers.
- Keep data access in `src/lib/*` or route handlers; never call Prisma directly from deeply nested UI components.
- For DB-backed pages, set explicit rendering strategy (`dynamic` or cache/revalidate) to avoid accidental build-time failures.
- Each route should provide graceful fallback UI when DB is unavailable.
- API routes return structured JSON with stable keys and HTTP status.
- Keep environment variables explicit: `DATABASE_URL`, `POSTGRES_*`, `VPS_*`.
- Production build must pass `npm run lint` and `npm run build` before deployment.
